-- Bicycle Thieves Target Muenster, Bern and Bremen, Study by Geld.de Shows
-- B y   Z o e   S c h n e e w e i s s
-- 2010-10-11T09:40:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/bicycle-thieves-target-muenster-bern-and-bremen-study-by-geld-de-shows.html
The German city of Muenster, in the
western state of North Rhine-Westphalia, leads a ranking of
bicycle thefts in the 60 biggest cities in Germany, Switzerland
and Austria for 2009, according to a  study  by Geld.de.  Bern, the Swiss capital, is second, Basel in Switzerland is
third and Bremen in Germany is fourth, according to the study, 
which ranks the cities according to thefts per 100,000 
inhabitants. Berlin is ranked at number 25 and Vienna at 
number 36.  Bicycle thefts in the 60 cities came in at 148,956 in 2009,
while in total more than 400,000 cycles were stolen in Germany,
Switzerland and Austria last year, Geld.de said in an e-mailed
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoe Schneeweiss at 
 zschneeweiss@bloomberg.net  